# About screen.

MainScreen:
    name: 'About'
    fullscreen: True

    GridLayout:
        cols: 1
        spacing: '8dp'

        RstDocument:
            text:
                ('Welcome \n'
                '======= \n'
                '\n'
                'Links App, Alpha v0.0.1 \n'
                '+++++++++++++++++++++++ \n'
                '\n\n'
                'Greetings, and welcome to the Alpha Dev release of the Official '
                'Multi Platform Links app. This project is being developed in Python '
                'using the cross-platform Kivy Library https://kivy.org/#home. '
                '(Source https://github.com/kivy/kivy) ' 
                'which can be compiled into the appropriate file type for various '
                'machine architectures. (See "Buildozer" https://github.com/kivy/buildozer \n\n'
                'Kivy installation instructions can be found here '
                'https://kivy.org/docs/gettingstarted/installation.html. '
                "Install on windows can be tricky but it's possible. Installation on linux is much easier. \n\n"
                'Kivy allows us to completely seperate the design from the functionality '
                'of the app by way of the extremely easy to use .kv language files. '
                "Therefore if you wish to help but aren't particularly comfortable "
                "coding it's no problem. See https://kivy.org/docs/api-kivy.lang.html. \n\n"
                'Custom created .kv files will be autoloaded for use when placed into '
                'the ./data/screens/ directory. \n\n' 
                "All modules are loaded this way (Including this About file, see "
                "./screens/about.kv) \n\n"
                "*Code can be viewed from the app by clicking on the bug icon "
                "in the upper right of the main window.* \n\n"
                "Kivy also allows for dynamic access to java or android modules with the Pyjnius "
                "library (See https://github.com/kivy/pyjnius) \n\n"
                '***Voice support still needs to be added.*** (See https://github.com/cidermole/audiostream) \n\n'
                'This project will be hosted on GitHub at https://github.com/Duroktar/links_android_dev '
                'Please do any error reporting or requests, etc. in the issues tab of '
                'the Github and please try to be helpful and respectful to everyone involved. \n\n'
                'Pull requests or merges will be more frequent in the beginning until '
                'the release of the Beta, at which time the release structure will be '
                'reviewed. '
                '\n\n'
                'Thanks for showing your interest and suport. If you would like to '
                'contact me directly my e-mail is duroktar@gmail.com and I will try to '
                'respond as quickly as possible '
                '\n\n'
                'Created by: traBpUkciP \n')
